This is one of the listed examples of the [Distributive Conditional
Types](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/advanced-types.html#distributive-conditional-types)
examples on the &quot;Advanced Types&quot; page of the Typescript handbook.

&gt; Conditional types are particularly useful when combined with mapped types:
 
&gt; ```typescript
&gt; type FunctionPropertyNames&lt;T&gt; = { [K in keyof T]: T[K] extends Function ? K : never }[keyof T];
&gt; type FunctionProperties&lt;T&gt; = Pick&lt;T, FunctionPropertyNames&lt;T&gt;&gt;;
&gt; 
&gt; type NonFunctionPropertyNames&lt;T&gt; = { [K in keyof T]: T[K] extends Function ? never : K }[keyof T];
&gt; type NonFunctionProperties&lt;T&gt; = Pick&lt;T, NonFunctionPropertyNames&lt;T&gt;&gt;;
&gt; 
&gt; interface Part {
&gt;     id: number;
&gt;     name: string;
&gt;     subparts: Part[];
&gt;     updatePart(newName: string): void;
&gt; }
&gt; 
&gt; type T40 = FunctionPropertyNames&lt;Part&gt;;  // &quot;updatePart&quot;
&gt; type T41 = NonFunctionPropertyNames&lt;Part&gt;;  // &quot;id&quot; | &quot;name&quot; | &quot;subparts&quot;
&gt; type T42 = FunctionProperties&lt;Part&gt;;  // { updatePart(newName: string): void }
&gt; type T43 = NonFunctionProperties&lt;Part&gt;;  // { id: number, name: string, subparts: Part[] }
&gt; ```

[A quick search of the Typescript Github repo](https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/search?q=NonFunctionProperties&amp;unscoped_q=NonFunctionProperties) reveals that this type is not currently a built-in utility type (unlike the undocumented types [`Parameters&lt;T&gt;` and `ConstructorParameters&lt;T&gt;`](https://github.com/microsoft/TypeScript/blob/v3.6.3/src/lib/es5.d.ts#L1456-L1464)), so you&#39;ll have to define the `NonFunctionProperties` equivalent yourself.

